  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">A box of contributions for the Boston bazaar is to leave Liverpool on the 19th. It contains a small parcel for Henry C. Wright, containing a purse worked for him by Mrs. Mary Welsh. Interest in the anti-slavery cause &quot;keeps up wonderfully here.&quot; Mary Welsh speaks disparagingly of the clergy, who &quot;remain silent and indifferent.&quot; She encloses an invoice from Glasgow; the Perth box accompanies the Glasgow ones.</subfield>
